JOHANNESBURG - The DA in the Free State will lay criminal charges against ANC Secretary General, Ace Magashule. The party alleged the former Free State premier meddled in a housing project to ensure that a company linked to his daughter secured a lucrative contract. The contract is worth around R150-million. The procurement processes were allegedly flouted to ensure that Unital Holdings was paid nearly R70-million. READ: Free State didn't spend Winnie museum funds: Magashule Magashule is also currently under scrutiny over the Winnie Madikizela-Mandela museum in Brandfort, which has not been completed, 11 years after work began on the project. He is accused of siphoning off the money. eNCA